title: Levels of N-13 near 7 MeV excitation (I).

x4freetext: Levels of N-13 near 7 MeV excitation (I).
Two surface-barrier counters. One counter was
used for laboratory angles from 35 to 155 degr. The
second counter was placed at an angle of 155 degr. to
the beam and was used as a monitor for elastically
scattered protons, enabling allowance to be made for
slight variations in target thickness during runs.
A thin (1.5 keV) self-supporting carbon foil.
